      <lg xml:id="MuTA79">
<l>ōrtta maṉattarā yaintaṭakki yārāyntu</l>
<l>pērttāṟ piṟappēḻum pērkkalāṅ – kārtta</l>
<l>viraiyār naṟuntuḻāy vīṅkōta mēṉi</l>
<l>niraiyāra mārpaṉaiyē niṉṟu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>If, as people with concentrated minds, they restrain the five [senses], examine</l>
<l>[and] destroy<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">The verbal noun in -(t)tal knows a rarer alternative form for 11th-class verbs with -kkal as a suffix, i.e., pērkkal instead of pērttal.</note> [them], there will be destruction of all the seven births</l>
<l>– constantly [concentrated] on the one whose chest has rows of garlands,</l>
<l>with the complexion of the swelling flood, with dark, fragrant tulsi full of scent.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
